WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:03:04.065 --> 00:03:05.984
- How long will you be?
- Oh. I don't know.

3
00:03:06.668 --> 00:03:08.114
Uh. not very long.

4
00:03:21.234 --> 00:03:24.704
Carol?

5
00:03:25.600 --> 00:03:26.394
Yes. Are you Michael?

6
00:03:26.456 --> 00:03:27.832
Yes.
Nice to meet you.

7
00:03:28.351 --> 00:03:31.536
- Am I late?
- Not at all.

8
00:03:31.590 --> 00:03:32.788
Brian was right. You are lovely.

9
00:03:33.186 --> 00:03:34.645
Thank you.

10
00:03:34.875 --> 00:03:37.178
Uh. our dinner reservations
aren't until 9:00.

11
00:03:37.408 --> 00:03:39.941
- Would you like a drink?
- Sure.

12
00:03:40.209 --> 00:03:40.670
You didn't have to drive.

13
00:03:40.862 --> 00:03:42.627
I'd have been happy to pick you up.

14
00:03:42.819 --> 00:03:45.390
Sometimes I have to work late.

15
00:03:45.582 --> 00:03:47.846
Anyway. I prefer to drive myself.

16
00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:50.188
In case you need a quick getaway?

17
00:03:50.379 --> 00:03:53.508
Blind dates can be a bit grim sometimes.

18
00:03:57.594 --> 00:03:58.822
Ever since Brian joined the firm.

19
00:03:59.014 --> 00:04:02.076
he's been trying to marry me off.

20
00:04:02.216 --> 00:04:03.773
Are you divorced?

21
00:04:03.965 --> 00:04:05.654
Uh. widower.

22
00:04:05.846 --> 00:04:09.606
- I'm sorry.
- No. that's all right.

23
00:04:09.837 --> 00:04:11.871
What kind of work do you do?

24
00:04:12.024 --> 00:04:13.790
I work with a publishing company.

25
00:04:13.943 --> 00:04:15.478
I'm one of many editors.

26
00:04:15.747 --> 00:04:17.090
It's no big deal.

27
00:04:17.282 --> 00:04:21.388
I read manuscripts and
take work home at night.

28
00:04:21.580 --> 00:04:24.420
I've known Connie for years.

29
00:04:24.650 --> 00:04:25.418
After my divorce.

30
00:04:25.610 --> 00:04:28.258
she took me on as something of a project.

31
00:04:28.450 --> 00:04:31.059
She thinks I work too hard.

32
00:04:31.251 --> 00:04:32.288
I hope you don't mind my asking.

33
00:04:32.479 --> 00:04:38.198
but why did you accept a blind date?

34
00:04:39.080 --> 00:04:41.920
I don't know.

35
00:04:42.227 --> 00:04:43.801
Connie was seeing Brian.

36
00:04:43.993 --> 00:04:44.990
and the three of us

37
00:04:45.182 --> 00:04:47.140
had been out to dinner
a couple of times.

38
00:04:47.370 --> 00:04:49.519
He seemed like a nice guy.

39
00:04:49.711 --> 00:04:52.628
Connie said the senior partner
in Brian's law firm

40
00:04:52.819 --> 00:04:54.431
was coming to Los Angeles.

41
00:04:54.623 --> 00:04:57.502
and that you were some heavy-duty lawyer

42
00:04:57.693 --> 00:05:00.150
and a really nice guy.

43
00:05:00.341 --> 00:05:02.375
I said I was busy.

44
00:05:02.567 --> 00:05:04.064
She said. what did I have to lose?

45
00:05:04.256 --> 00:05:07.173
The worst thing that could happen is
I'd have a nice meal.

46
00:05:07.365 --> 00:05:09.936
Your friend's right.
Dinner will be very good.

47
00:05:10.128 --> 00:05:12.085
Mr. Tarlow?
Message for you. sir.

48
00:05:12.354 --> 00:05:16.575
Thank you.
Excuse me.

49
00:05:17.726 --> 00:05:20.374
Oh.

50
00:05:20.566 --> 00:05:22.946
I have to go upstairs
and make a phone call.

51
00:05:23.176 --> 00:05:27.129
- Anything serious?
- No. Just an anxious client.

52
00:05:27.321 --> 00:05:27.589
Would you like to come up?

53
00:05:27.820 --> 00:05:30.583
I won't be very long.

54
00:05:30.504 --> 00:05:32.726
I know it sounds fishy.

55
00:05:33.575 --> 00:05:34.459
If you prefer to stay down here.

56
00:05:34.651 --> 00:05:37.551
I'll just be a little while.

57
00:05:39.179 --> 00:05:41.468
No. It's all right.
I'll come.

58
00:05:48.428 --> 00:05:50.731
- Wow. this is beautiful.
- It is. isn't it?

59
00:05:50.923 --> 00:05:52.475
Have a look around.
I'll just be a minute.

60
00:06:07.962 --> 00:06:09.588
Yeah. hi. it's Tarlow.
Is he there?

61
00:06:13.757 --> 00:06:16.597
Are you sure?
I got a message to call him.

62
00:06:16.713 --> 00:06:18.555
Tell him I returned his call. OK?

63
00:06:18.747 --> 00:06:21.586
Thank you. Bye.

64
00:06:27.995 --> 00:06:29.876
Leo.

65
00:06:30.068 --> 00:06:31.541
I just got a message to call you.

66
00:06:32.243 --> 00:06:33.300
Hello. Michael.

67
00:06:35.019 --> 00:06:37.382
I thought you were in New Orleans.

68
00:06:37.417 --> 00:06:38.818
Yeah. but...

69
00:06:39.048 --> 00:06:42.579
I decided to come home a day early.

70
00:06:42.771 --> 00:06:44.037
I wish you would have let me know.

71
00:06:44.268 --> 00:06:45.956
I'd have given you a call.

72
00:06:46.148 --> 00:06:49.909
There's no need for that now. is there?

73
00:06:50.178 --> 00:06:51.789
You going to invite us in?

74
00:06:51.981 --> 00:06:55.129
Uh. yeah. Sure. Excuse me.

75
00:07:01.606 --> 00:07:03.149
Wootton. this is Michael Tarlow.

76
00:07:03.379 --> 00:07:06.450
my lawyer.
Michael. Jack Wootton.

77
00:07:06.603 --> 00:07:08.867
How do you do?

78
00:07:09.059 --> 00:07:10.239
Sit down.
Can I get you something to drink?

79
00:07:11.515 --> 00:07:12.695
No. thank you.

80
00:07:12.695 --> 00:07:16.236
- I take it you've been busy.
- Yeah.

81
00:07:15.652 --> 00:07:16.885
What brings you to Los Angeles?

82
00:07:17.272 --> 00:07:18.903
I'm closing the Gallway deal.

83
00:07:18.976 --> 00:07:20.918
I should have papers on your desk soon.

84
00:07:22.443 --> 00:07:25.428
You didn't have to come here.
You could have called.

85
00:07:27.793 --> 00:07:27.979
When you do things face to face.

86
00:07:28.171 --> 00:07:30.013
it's a lot clearer.

87
00:07:30.205 --> 00:07:31.316
I agree.

88
00:07:33.949 --> 00:07:35.366
You seem edgy. Michael.

89
00:07:35.591 --> 00:07:37.498
- That's not like you.
- I'm fine.

90
00:07:44.282 --> 00:07:46.460
What can I do for you?

91
00:07:46.891 --> 00:07:49.480
I have a problem.
I need your advice.

92
00:07:49.604 --> 00:07:51.916
- That's what you pay me for.
- That's right.

93
00:07:51.916 --> 00:07:54.736
That's what I pay you for.

94
00:07:54.736 --> 00:07:56.289
There's a man who works for me.

95
00:07:57.295 --> 00:07:58.927
He's close to me. I trusted him.

96
00:07:58.990 --> 00:08:00.499
So what's the problem?

97
00:08:00.499 --> 00:08:04.549
He got himself into some
financial trouble.

98
00:08:04.549 --> 00:08:05.746
He made some investments.

99
00:08:08.183 --> 00:08:10.277
He leveraged himself up to his eyeballs.

100
00:08:10.396 --> 00:08:12.077
The investments didn't work out.

101
00:08:12.896 --> 00:08:14.337
He got himself in serious debt.

102
00:08:15.151 --> 00:08:17.545
He didn't come to me and
tell me his problem.

103
00:08:17.545 --> 00:08:19.668
He didn't come to the man
who trusted him

104
00:08:19.668 --> 00:08:21.201
And ask for help.

105
00:08:21.201 --> 00:08:24.692
What he did was. he just took my money.

106
00:08:24.692 --> 00:08:26.468
took a lot of it.

107
00:08:26.468 --> 00:08:30.083
He was very clever.
so it was very hard to find out about.

108
00:08:30.647 --> 00:08:32.425
I need your advice. Michael.

109
00:08:32.425 --> 00:08:34.302
What should I do with this man?

110
00:08:37.069 --> 00:08:37.899
Leo ...

111
00:08:38.202 --> 00:08:39.615
What do you think?

112
00:08:39.944 --> 00:08:43.824
- What would you do?
- Now. you don't understand. Leo.

113
00:08:43.824 --> 00:08:45.633
- I understand.
- I can explain it.

114
00:08:46.361 --> 00:08:48.930
Good.
I would like you to.

115
00:08:50.908 --> 00:08:53.508
It's not what you think. I would never ...

116
00:08:53.610 --> 00:08:54.416
Please. Michael.

117
00:08:54.595 --> 00:08:57.146
Have enough respect for me not to lie.

118
00:09:05.063 --> 00:09:06.104
I ...

119
00:09:06.139 --> 00:09:07.799
I was desperate. Leo.

120
00:09:08.613 --> 00:09:10.752
I took some funds from
the con-amalgamate account ...

121
00:09:12.732 --> 00:09:14.047
To cover a loan. I ...

122
00:09:16.434 --> 00:09:18.651
I was going to pay you back.
I swear!

123
00:09:19.229 --> 00:09:21.360
I'm so disappointed in you. Michael.

124
00:09:22.676 --> 00:09:26.380
For God's sake. you got to believe me.
You know I'd pay you back. Leo.

125
00:09:27.079 --> 00:09:28.605
Michael. don't be afraid.

126
00:09:28.605 --> 00:09:31.288
You're acting like you think
I'll harm you.

127
00:09:31.977 --> 00:09:52.658
Michael ...

128
00:09:36.467 --> 00:09:38.002
Even though you betrayed me.

129
00:09:38.156 --> 00:09:39.652
and I trusted you.

130
00:09:39.844 --> 00:09:42.646
I would never harm you.

131
00:09:42.838 --> 00:09:45.294
Here's what you're going to do.

132
00:09:45.324 --> 00:09:48.087
You're going to go back to New York.

133
00:09:48.279 --> 00:09:50.889
Someone else will close
the Gallway deal.

134
00:09:51.119 --> 00:09:53.383
I will never do business with you again.

135
00:09:53.575 --> 00:09:56.324
You'll pay me back what
you owe with interest.

136
00:09:57.259 --> 00:09:58.641
If you have to sell your nice apartment

137
00:09:58.833 --> 00:10:01.136
with the David Hockneys on the wall.

138
00:10:01.327 --> 00:10:02.556
then you'll do that.

139
00:10:02.824 --> 00:10:04.705
You will pay me back.

140
00:10:04.897 --> 00:10:07.583
I will never speak to you again.

141
00:10:07.737 --> 00:10:08.427
You're right. Michael.

142
00:10:08.619 --> 00:10:10.845
It's better to talk these things
over face to face.

143
00:10:11.037 --> 00:10:12.161
It's clearer that way.

144
00:10:15.273 --> 00:10:17.723
Goodbye. Michael.
Don't get up.

145
00:10:20.147 --> 00:10:21.684
Oh. Michael?

146
00:10:22.525 --> 00:10:23.876
I lied.

147
00:12:45.612 --> 00:12:46.123
Yeah?

148
00:12:49.659 --> 00:12:50.508
Caulfield here.

149
00:12:52.793 --> 00:12:53.383
What?

150
00:12:55.171 --> 00:12:56.492
How soon can you be here?

151
00:12:57.494 --> 00:12:58.923
Five minutes is too long.

152
00:12:59.862 --> 00:13:00.922
Right.

153
00:13:14.306 --> 00:13:15.575
He's in a conference.

154
00:13:15.648 --> 00:13:16.326
Right.

155
00:13:19.871 --> 00:13:21.849
Good morning.
Won't you come in?

156
00:13:22.303 --> 00:13:23.033
Martin. James.

157
00:13:23.533 --> 00:13:24.518
Detective Sergeant Benti.

158
00:13:25.018 --> 00:13:26.649
Nice meeting you.
This is James Dahlbeck.

159
00:13:26.737 --> 00:13:28.591
Like Caulfield. he's a Deputy D. A.

160
00:13:29.541 --> 00:13:31.344
We were discussing his trial tomorrow.

161
00:13:31.536 --> 00:13:33.862
That's why my door was closed.

162
00:13:33.971 --> 00:13:36.172
I believe it's called a conference.

163
00:13:37.230 --> 00:13:38.712
Remember those latents we found

164
00:13:38.712 --> 00:13:40.815
on the bathroom glass in Michael Tarlow's suite?

165
00:13:40.815 --> 00:13:42.724
Yes. They never checked out.

166
00:13:43.296 --> 00:13:44.494
They didn't check out in California.

167
00:13:44.553 --> 00:13:47.460
But Detective Sergeant Benti's been hard at work.

168
00:13:47.890 --> 00:13:49.253
I'm impressed.

169
00:13:48.791 --> 00:13:50.046
Go ahead. Detective Sergeant.

170
00:13:50.357 --> 00:13:51.410
Make me look good.

171
00:13:54.725 --> 00:13:56.676
We ran those prints
through the federal computer.

172
00:13:57.515 --> 00:13:58.994
They belong to Carol Hunnicut.

173
00:13:58.994 --> 00:14:01.569
arrested for disorderly conduct in 1981.

174
00:14:01.569 --> 00:14:03.501
some kind of anti-nuke bullshit.

175
00:14:03.953 --> 00:14:05.231
She works for a publishing company.

176
00:14:05.461 --> 00:14:08.301
She's been absent since Tarlow got iced.

177
00:14:08.532 --> 00:14:10.622
- This is riveting.
- He'll get your attention.

178
00:14:10.651 --> 00:14:12.177
I checked through our logs.

179
00:14:12.212 --> 00:14:14.697
Two days after Tarlow died. we got a call.

180
00:14:14.954 --> 00:14:20.314
Constance Billings said her friend
was missing.

181
00:14:19.292 --> 00:14:21.682
We told her to file
a missing persons report.

182
00:14:21.893 --> 00:14:25.180
She changed her mind.
said maybe her friend left for a while.

183
00:14:25.438 --> 00:14:27.334
She never gave us the friend's full name.

184
00:14:27.590 --> 00:14:29.525
just the first. Carol.

185
00:14:29.525 --> 00:14:31.262
- Still with us so far?
- I'm holding my own.

186
00:14:31.885 --> 00:14:34.947
I got Constance's address
and went to see her.

187
00:14:35.019 --> 00:14:38.732
Early this morning.
Before they've had their coffee.

188
00:14:38.732 --> 00:14:39.769
they rattle easier.

189
00:14:42.758 --> 00:14:44.142
She didn't want to see me from nothing.

190
00:14:44.142 --> 00:14:46.000
She said she didn't know anything.

191
00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:47.487
She had total amnesia.

192
00:14:47.487 --> 00:14:49.529
She was scared shitless.

193
00:14:49.529 --> 00:14:52.024
I told her we'd protect her and her friend.

194
00:14:51.514 --> 00:14:53.426
We couldn't protect her if she didn't.

195
00:14:53.438 --> 00:14:55.579
She was as easy to crack as a raw egg.

196
00:14:55.579 --> 00:14:57.534
Then she comes out with it.

197
00:14:58.225 --> 00:14:59.413
The reason why

198
00:14:59.413 --> 00:15:01.767
Hunnicut's fingerprints
were on the glass

199
00:15:02.070 --> 00:15:05.311
is because she was there
when Tarlow got hit.

200
00:15:06.117 --> 00:15:07.904
She saw it.
She was there.

201
00:15:09.787 --> 00:15:10.809
It gets better.

202
00:15:16.669 --> 00:15:17.960
It gets a lot better.

203
00:15:20.532 --> 00:15:23.231
- You're kidding?
- Leo fucking Watts.

204
00:15:23.254 --> 00:15:25.020
In person.
In living colour.

205
00:15:25.272 --> 00:15:26.730
The woman was in the other room.

206
00:15:26.730 --> 00:15:28.792
She saw everything.
Everything.

207
00:15:28.863 --> 00:15:31.142
- Nobody knew about her.
- Where is she?

208
00:15:31.219 --> 00:15:33.100
She understandably freaked and took off.

209
00:15:33.219 --> 00:15:35.737
She called her friend.
told her what happened.

210
00:15:36.176 --> 00:15:37.594
and that she was still alive.

211
00:15:37.868 --> 00:15:41.093
She's hiding out in a cabin in East Jesus.

212
00:15:41.856 --> 00:15:43.798
- There is a God.
- Unbelievable.

213
00:15:43.857 --> 00:15:46.367
I've chartered a plane.
It'll fly to a small strip.

214
00:15:46.367 --> 00:15:48.814
A helicopter will fly us where she is.

215
00:15:48.814 --> 00:15:50.614
I'll pick her up.
Come back the same way.

216
00:15:51.179 --> 00:15:52.721
Nobody knows anything about her.

217
00:15:53.859 --> 00:15:56.343
Leo's in for a nice surprise.
Meantime. get your warrant.

218
00:15:56.343 --> 00:15:58.392
- What if she won't talk?
- She'll talk.

219
00:15:59.167 --> 00:16:01.752
- You know this for a fact?
- I'll promise her protection.

220
00:16:01.752 --> 00:16:03.546
I'll offer her relocation.

221
00:16:03.546 --> 00:16:04.502
She has to talk.

222
00:16:05.265 --> 00:16:07.040
Shouldn't you find out
if she'll cooperate?

223
00:16:07.040 --> 00:16:10.158
There's no phone.
She might just take off.

224
00:16:10.158 --> 00:16:11.929
- Where is this place?
- In Canada.

225
00:16:12.725 --> 00:16:13.994
I can't authorize this

226
00:16:13.994 --> 00:16:16.266
without checking with the director
of branch and area operations.

227
00:16:16.266 --> 00:16:18.098
I have to follow procedure.

228
00:16:18.779 --> 00:16:19.793
This is Leo Watts.

229
00:16:19.793 --> 00:16:21.633
We've got him for Murder One.

230
00:16:21.633 --> 00:16:22.958
You understand what that means?

231
00:16:22.958 --> 00:16:26.204
I do. I still have to check.

232
00:16:26.204 --> 00:16:28.695
- What's the matter with you?
- Nothing.

233
00:16:29.195 --> 00:16:30.305
Why are you doing this again?

234
00:16:30.805 --> 00:16:33.684
- Doing what?
- Last year we had him.

235
00:16:33.684 --> 00:16:35.589
You put me in your bureaucratic blender.

236
00:16:35.589 --> 00:16:39.136
- and we lost him.
- You had uncorroborated statements

237
00:16:40.506 --> 00:16:40.666
from an informant doing hard time

238
00:16:40.666 --> 00:16:42.994
who'd sell his own mother.

239
00:16:42.994 --> 00:16:43.348
In fact. he did try that.

240
00:16:45.318 --> 00:16:48.350
except his mother had been dead
for 10 years.

241
00:16:48.706 --> 00:16:49.769
You want to make the announcement?

242
00:16:52.181 --> 00:16:54.706
Television cameras are an aphrodisiac to you.

243
00:16:54.706 --> 00:16:56.373
You could be on the news.

244
00:16:56.373 --> 00:16:58.450
Does that satisfy you?

245
00:17:01.807 --> 00:17:03.629
Our job is to convict criminals.

246
00:17:03.629 --> 00:17:06.044
not to have them acquitted.

247
00:17:06.044 --> 00:17:08.437
I'll conduct business in a proper way.

248
00:17:08.437 --> 00:17:09.482
whether it pleases you or not.

249
00:17:09.482 --> 00:17:13.322
I don't like the implications
of what you're saying.

250
00:17:16.120 --> 00:17:18.960
Let's go.

251
00:17:19.692 --> 00:17:20.444
We're going.

252
00:17:22.207 --> 00:17:23.374
We're going now.

253
00:17:23.374 --> 00:17:25.446
Not without my authorization.

254
00:17:41.716 --> 00:17:43.279
Why does he have to fly so low?

255
00:17:44.059 --> 00:17:46.740
We're not low.
The ground's high.

256
00:17:48.013 --> 00:17:50.715
See?
Now we're high.

257
00:17:51.361 --> 00:17:52.632
I hate these things.

258
00:17:53.008 --> 00:17:55.984
Sorry. sir.
A little turbulence in the thermals

259
00:17:55.984 --> 00:17:57.378
on the mountain's windward side.

260
00:17:57.594 --> 00:17:58.801
I don't want to know about thermals.

261
00:17:58.853 --> 00:18:03.761
You have to admit.
the scenery's spectacular.

262
00:18:03.761 --> 00:18:05.460
If I want scenery. I'll get a postcard.

263
00:18:05.567 --> 00:18:08.633
- How much longer?
- We'll be there in five minutes.

264
00:18:08.641 --> 00:18:11.013
- That's too long.
- What does she look like?

265
00:18:12.187 --> 00:18:15.108
I don't care what she looks like.
I don't like the company she keeps.

266
00:18:17.065 --> 00:18:18.495
You realize when we go down.

267
00:18:18.671 --> 00:18:20.780
nobody will find us except
some fucking moose.

268
00:18:22.417 --> 00:18:25.233
You think top gun up there can tell
if somebody's following us?

269
00:18:26.306 --> 00:18:27.865
Like what. a condor?

270
00:18:31.118 --> 00:18:32.493
There it is.

271
00:18:49.788 --> 00:18:51.644
Keep the motor running. OK?

272
00:19:02.312 --> 00:19:03.180
It's warm.

273
00:19:15.204 --> 00:19:16.262
Miss Hunnicut?

274
00:19:17.434 --> 00:19:19.406
I'm Detective Sergeant Dominick Benti.

275
00:19:19.406 --> 00:19:20.466
Los Angeles Police Department.

276
00:19:21.700 --> 00:19:24.663
With me is Deputy District
Attorney Robert Caulfield.

277
00:19:28.078 --> 00:19:29.292
We know you're in there.

278
00:19:29.616 --> 00:19:31.671
We'll wait all day out here if we have to.

279
00:19:32.237 --> 00:19:34.215
Real cold out here.

280
00:19:34.225 --> 00:19:35.319
Hope we don't have to.

281
00:19:41.026 --> 00:19:42.512
Can I see some identification. please?

282
00:19:55.427 --> 00:19:56.241
What do you want?

283
00:19:57.574 --> 00:19:57.869
I think you know.

284
00:19:59.167 --> 00:20:00.258
I don't know what you're talking about.

285
00:20:01.028 --> 00:20:03.634
You were witness to a murder.
We'd like you to testify.

286
00:20:06.221 --> 00:20:07.753
I never saw anything.

287
00:20:09.705 --> 00:20:10.580
How did you find me?

288
00:20:10.580 --> 00:20:11.740
Constance Billings told us.

289
00:20:11.740 --> 00:20:14.316
She said you saw a lot.

290
00:20:14.653 --> 00:20:15.766
I have nothing to say.

291
00:20:17.238 --> 00:20:19.063
You wouldn't happen to have a drink.
would you?

292
00:20:20.228 --> 00:20:21.006
You're on duty.

293
00:20:21.006 --> 00:20:23.142
I only drink when I'm on duty.

294
00:20:23.843 --> 00:20:26.103
How do I know who you are?

295
00:20:26.412 --> 00:20:27.033
You saw our ID.

296
00:20:27.233 --> 00:20:29.138
It could be fake. I wouldn't know.

297
00:20:30.398 --> 00:20:31.557
If we were going to do you some harm.

298
00:20:31.557 --> 00:20:32.984
we'd have done it already.

299
00:20:40.398 --> 00:20:41.518
There's coffee on the stove.

300
00:20:42.437 --> 00:20:44.817
- Do you have any beer?
- No.

301
00:20:45.047 --> 00:20:46.275
Nice place.

302
00:20:46.367 --> 00:20:48.745
- Thanks.
- Jesus! She really doesn't have beer.

303
00:20:50.290 --> 00:20:52.973
Miss Hunnicut. we'd really like you to
come back and testify.

304
00:20:53.939 --> 00:20:55.462
I'm not going anywhere with you.

305
00:20:55.481 --> 00:20:57.333
I didn't see anything.
I don't know anything.

306
00:20:57.348 --> 00:20:58.911
I'm not going to testify.

307
00:20:59.591 --> 00:21:00.670
Aren't you pleasant.

308
00:21:00.714 --> 00:21:03.836
I really have nothing to say to you.

309
00:21:04.320 --> 00:21:06.535
- I'd like you to leave.
- You don't realize your situation.

310
00:21:06.890 --> 00:21:09.364
I know exactly the situation I'm in.

311
00:21:10.528 --> 00:21:12.294
I don't think you do.
We can protect you.

312
00:21:12.337 --> 00:21:13.732
If you stay here. they're gonna find you.

313
00:21:13.875 --> 00:21:15.895
There's no reason for anyone
to come after me.

314
00:21:16.391 --> 00:21:18.025
I'm not testifying.

315
00:21:18.902 --> 00:21:20.966
- I have a subpoena.
- Let me see it.

316
00:21:24.603 --> 00:21:25.285
I can get one.

317
00:21:25.935 --> 00:21:27.186
I think you should leave.

318
00:21:27.446 --> 00:21:29.049
Lady. you're kidding yourself.

319
00:21:29.595 --> 00:21:31.236
You think those guys would come up here.

320
00:21:31.359 --> 00:21:34.569
You. being the one who could put
Leo Watts in the gas chamber.

321
00:21:34.616 --> 00:21:36.570
and you tell them you're not testifying.

322
00:21:37.007 --> 00:21:39.279
and they'd say.
"Wow. that's a relief. Thanks."

323
00:21:39.279 --> 00:21:42.601
"You have a nice day."
Then they'd turn around and go home?

324
00:21:44.620 --> 00:21:45.546
They'd never find me.

325
00:21:45.673 --> 00:21:48.822
- We did.
- I'll take my chances.

326
00:21:58.675 --> 00:21:59.859
Do you have the keys to that car?

327
00:22:00.828 --> 00:22:01.292
On the table.

328
00:22:06.928 --> 00:22:08.553
I don't suppose there's a back door.
is there?

329
00:22:08.886 --> 00:22:11.568
- No.
- How about a window?

330
00:22:11.857 --> 00:22:13.811
Yes. It's in the bathroom.

331
00:22:42.754 --> 00:22:44.756
You get to that window. all right?

332
00:22:45.952 --> 00:22:48.005
Keep low. Wait for me there.

333
00:22:48.732 --> 00:22:50.865
Go! Go!

334
00:23:37.038 --> 00:23:37.771
Now!

335
00:24:03.574 --> 00:24:04.642
What have you done to me?

336
00:24:05.119 --> 00:24:06.228
Nobody knew where I was.

337
00:24:06.474 --> 00:24:10.481
Sorry. How could I know
they were following us.

338
00:24:10.374 --> 00:24:11.142
Aren't you supposed to?

339
00:24:11.177 --> 00:24:12.335
Isn't that your job?

340
00:24:12.557 --> 00:24:14.599
How could you let somebody follow you?

341
00:24:14.634 --> 00:24:16.909
Where's the closest telephone?

342
00:24:16.909 --> 00:24:18.766
8 miles down this road.

343
00:26:10.714 --> 00:26:12.775
The train's slowing down.
How far to the station?

344
00:26:13.015 --> 00:26:13.893
About a half mile.

345
00:27:27.969 --> 00:27:28.599
Let's go.

346
00:28:00.812 --> 00:28:01.521
Excuse me.

347
00:28:01.733 --> 00:28:02.834
Where's the closest big town?

348
00:28:02.834 --> 00:28:06.299
- I beg your pardon.
- A big city with an airport.

349
00:28:06.299 --> 00:28:07.268
Where's the nearest one?

350
00:28:07.268 --> 00:28:08.712
East. about 100 miles.

351
00:28:08.712 --> 00:28:12.077
- Which way is this train heading?
- West. of course.

352
00:28:12.077 --> 00:28:15.249
Vancouver's as big as you get.

353
00:28:15.249 --> 00:28:16.964
This train goes to Vancouver.

354
00:28:16.964 --> 00:28:20.106
- How long does that take?
- You arrive Vancouver 10:40 a.m.

355
00:28:20.106 --> 00:28:21.172
You're kidding?

356
00:28:21.172 --> 00:28:22.710
No. you're not kidding.

357
00:28:23.258 --> 00:28:26.006
I'd like a private compartment.

358
00:28:26.006 --> 00:28:28.278
Sorry. All we got left is coach seats.

359
00:28:28.278 --> 00:28:31.354
I have to have a private compartment.

360
00:28:31.354 --> 00:28:32.305
Then wait until tomorrow.

361
00:28:32.305 --> 00:28:35.458
I'll see if we got space on that train.

362
00:28:35.392 --> 00:28:37.514
You don't understand.
I have to be on that train.

363
00:28:42.338 --> 00:28:44.551
I'd like to help you out Mister.
There's nothing I can do.

364
00:28:44.816 --> 00:28:45.811
I have to lie down.

365
00:28:45.946 --> 00:28:47.029
She has to lie down.

366
00:28:47.029 --> 00:28:49.632
If I go into labour. I have to lie down.

367
00:28:49.632 --> 00:28:53.237
The baby isn't due
for another two weeks but ...

368
00:28:53.237 --> 00:28:56.153
- I have to lie down.
- Don't worry honey. it's OK.

369
00:28:56.625 --> 00:28:58.993
Pardon me sir. I couldn't help overhearing.

370
00:28:58.993 --> 00:29:01.217
My wife and I. we have a compartment.

371
00:29:01.217 --> 00:29:03.656
You kids looks as though
you need it more than we do.

372
00:29:03.656 --> 00:29:05.825
- We couldn't do that.
- Please. I insist.

373
00:29:05.825 --> 00:29:07.942
I remember how it was with our Mark.

374
00:29:07.942 --> 00:29:12.462
- Is this your first?
- Yes. That's very kind. Thank you.

375
00:29:12.462 --> 00:29:15.176
I'll pay for both tickets.
I insist.

376
00:29:15.176 --> 00:29:17.721
- Is there a phone on the train?
- Afraid not.

377
00:29:17.721 --> 00:29:20.024
$195. please.

378
00:29:22.831 --> 00:29:25.399
That's car 564. drawing room A.

379
00:29:25.399 --> 00:29:29.233
- It's toward the end of the train.
- Thank you.

380
00:29:33.446 --> 00:29:34.682
Get on the train.

381
00:29:34.682 --> 00:29:37.982
Don't wait for me.
Get in the room. lock the door.

382
00:29:37.982 --> 00:29:39.947
Don't let anybody in.

383
00:29:40.282 --> 00:29:43.318
They probably haven't seen you.
All right. Here.

384
00:29:43.318 --> 00:29:45.218
Go. Go.

385
00:29:51.587 --> 00:29:53.980
- I'm really very grateful.
- That's quite all right.

386
00:29:54.008 --> 00:29:55.470
Take care of the little lady.

387
00:32:13.721 --> 00:32:14.406
Yes?

388
00:32:15.543 --> 00:32:16.689
There's been some mistake.
This is my compartment.

389
00:32:17.189 --> 00:32:19.045
If there's a mistake. it's yours.

390
00:32:19.434 --> 00:32:21.033
- This is our compartment.
- You're sure?

391
00:32:21.033 --> 00:32:23.692
Yes. of course I'm sure.
Could you please excuse us?

392
00:32:23.692 --> 00:32:25.874
The conductor said this was mine.

393
00:32:25.874 --> 00:32:28.859
He couldn't have said that.
This is our compartment.

394
00:32:28.859 --> 00:32:32.059
- Could I see your ticket. please?
- Can I see yours?

395
00:32:32.059 --> 00:32:34.606
My wife has our tickets.

396
00:32:34.606 --> 00:32:37.350
Well. maybe your wife is
in the proper car.

397
00:32:37.350 --> 00:32:40.094
This is my son. This is not your wife.

398
00:32:40.094 --> 00:32:42.368
This is our compartment. Not your compartment.

399
00:32:42.403 --> 00:32:43.691
I would like you to leave.

400
00:32:44.068 --> 00:32:45.300
This guy's lying.

401
00:32:46.543 --> 00:32:48.314
I'm sorry for the inconvenience. really.

402
00:32:48.552 --> 00:32:50.437
I'm always getting myself
into these kinds of things.

403
00:32:51.419 --> 00:32:55.005
One time. I. uh. I lost my car.

404
00:32:55.218 --> 00:32:56.638
I parked it in a parking lot

405
00:32:56.673 --> 00:32:59.799
And forgot where I parked it.
I just ...

406
00:33:00.805 --> 00:33:02.120
You know what that's like.

407
00:33:02.222 --> 00:33:04.877
No. I don't know what that's like.
Would you please get out of here?

408
00:33:04.978 --> 00:33:06.402
Yes. of course. I'm sorry.

409
00:33:15.235 --> 00:33:17.194
Is this car 564?

410
00:33:17.251 --> 00:33:17.532
No.

411
00:33:18.133 --> 00:33:21.135
Well. there you are.
See? I've done it again.

412
00:33:21.207 --> 00:33:23.439
I'm supposed to be in car 564.

413
00:33:23.439 --> 00:33:25.813
Maybe you should go to car 564.

414
00:33:25.813 --> 00:33:28.046
Would you know where that is?

415
00:33:28.046 --> 00:33:28.944
No. I wouldn't.

416
00:33:30.487 --> 00:33:32.819
He's lying. Mom. He's a train robber.

417
00:33:32.819 --> 00:33:34.553
What would I want with a train?

418
00:33:34.753 --> 00:33:35.659
Do you have a gun?

419
00:33:35.922 --> 00:33:38.077
I guess I'll see the conductor.

420
00:33:38.077 --> 00:33:41.130
He'd know where car 564 is.
wouldn't you think?

421
00:33:41.174 --> 00:33:45.089
I'd expect so. Why don't you do that?

422
00:33:45.089 --> 00:33:48.369
I'll go find him and ask him
where car 564 really is.

423
00:33:48.668 --> 00:33:53.601
- Good idea.
- Well. uh. sorry for the inconvenience.

424
00:33:58.039 --> 00:34:00.712
- You folks have a nice trip.
- You. too.

425
00:34:08.621 --> 00:34:10.582
It's me ... Caulfield

426
00:34:13.640 --> 00:34:15.303
How you doing?
I've been better.

427
00:34:15.303 --> 00:34:16.799
Yeah. me. too.

428
00:34:17.299 --> 00:34:19.016
So. are we expecting company?

429
00:34:19.016 --> 00:34:20.295
There's two of them.

430
00:34:20.295 --> 00:34:22.255
It won't take them long
to find this compartment.

431
00:34:26.315 --> 00:34:28.579
I'm getting off at the next stop.

432
00:34:28.579 --> 00:34:30.087
That's impossible.

433
00:34:30.087 --> 00:34:31.922
- You watch me.
- We'd be sitting ducks out there.

434
00:34:31.922 --> 00:34:35.111
Who said anything about we?

435
00:34:35.251 --> 00:34:36.787
You're going out there alone?

436
00:34:39.202 --> 00:34:41.157
We're in the middle of
a god-damn wilderness.

437
00:34:41.157 --> 00:34:43.891
Look out the window. for Christ's sakes.

438
00:34:43.891 --> 00:34:47.228
You're going out there on foot?
A breeze.

439
00:34:47.228 --> 00:34:49.400
I can protect you better here.

440
00:34:49.400 --> 00:34:52.259
Protect me?
You're the one who put me in danger.

441
00:34:55.724 --> 00:34:57.681
I'm not stupid. Mr. Caulfield.

442
00:34:58.792 --> 00:35:01.862
I won't survive stuck on this train
until tomorrow.

443
00:35:03.483 --> 00:35:06.279
Let me tell you something.
A police officer died

444
00:35:06.279 --> 00:35:08.192
trying to help get you back
to Los Angeles.

445
00:35:10.294 --> 00:35:11.619
I'm going to get you back there.

446
00:35:11.619 --> 00:35:15.087
I can't tell you what a comfort that is.

447
00:35:15.087 --> 00:35:18.917
- I don't think I like you.
- The weekend in Paris is off?

448
00:35:18.917 --> 00:35:22.401
You got a big mouth.
Use it on the witness stand.

449
00:35:22.401 --> 00:35:24.489
I don't think you hear very well.

450
00:35:24.489 --> 00:35:26.883
I'm not testifying at this trial.

451
00:35:26.883 --> 00:35:28.219
You still don't get it.

452
00:35:28.219 --> 00:35:30.574
These guys are grown-ups
with automatic weapons.

453
00:35:30.574 --> 00:35:33.078
If they see you. they'll kill you.

454
00:35:33.078 --> 00:35:35.333
We got two things going for us ...

455
00:35:35.333 --> 00:35:37.967
One. they've seen me. but maybe not you.

456
00:35:37.967 --> 00:35:39.723
They might not recognize you.

457
00:35:39.723 --> 00:35:44.350
- And?
- And... we got one thing going for us.

458
00:35:44.350 --> 00:35:45.906
But I've got you to protect me.

459
00:35:49.897 --> 00:35:51.698
- Who is it?
- The conductor. sir.

460
00:35:52.280 --> 00:35:53.508
Uh. yes?

461
00:35:54.273 --> 00:35:55.855
I'm sorry to disturb you.

462
00:35:55.855 --> 00:35:58.042
A gentleman has lost his briefcase.

463
00:35:59.459 --> 00:35:59.974
Yeah.

464
00:36:06.071 --> 00:36:09.486
Well. we think the porter
may have left it

465
00:36:09.486 --> 00:36:11.774
in one of these compartments by mistake.

466
00:36:11.774 --> 00:36:13.314
We're checking the whole car.

467
00:36:13.314 --> 00:36:14.551
It's not in here.

468
00:36:14.551 --> 00:36:17.186
You're welcome to take a look
if you'd like.

469
00:36:17.186 --> 00:36:18.049
Thank you.

470
00:36:23.417 --> 00:36:26.099
Hmm. I guess It's not in here.

471
00:36:26.099 --> 00:36:27.085
I guess not.

472
00:36:27.085 --> 00:36:29.703
I'm sure it's in this car some-place.

473
00:36:29.703 --> 00:36:31.365
Maybe not.

474
00:36:34.103 --> 00:36:35.252
We'll keep looking.

475
00:36:35.252 --> 00:36:37.866
I'm sorry to have bothered you. sir.

476
00:36:45.982 --> 00:36:48.174
- He'll be back. won't he?
- Yeah.

477
00:36:49.181 --> 00:36:51.060
- How do we stop him?
- We don't.

478
00:36:52.095 --> 00:36:53.612
Want me to set out some hors d'oeuvres?

479
00:36:53.612 --> 00:36:56.827
I want you to do exactly
what I tell you to do.

480
00:38:42.546 --> 00:38:43.681
Excuse me.
I wasn't looking where I was going.

481
00:38:43.894 --> 00:38:45.081
That's quite all right. sir.

482
00:38:46.477 --> 00:38:48.745
Operator. I want to make a collect call
to James Dahlbeck.

483
00:38:48.779 --> 00:38:51.806
My name is Caulfield C-a-u-l-f-i-e-l-d.

484
00:39:07.573 --> 00:39:09.781
Caulfield. where the hell are you?

485
00:39:10.101 --> 00:39:11.748
- I'm on a train.
- You're on a what?

486
00:39:11.748 --> 00:39:14.760
We were followed. Sergeant Benti's dead.

487
00:39:14.760 --> 00:39:18.549
It seems strange.
Larner doesn't want to send me here.

488
00:39:18.549 --> 00:39:19.784
Then we're followed.

489
00:39:19.784 --> 00:39:21.730
- You're way off base.
- Think so?

490
00:39:21.730 --> 00:39:24.783
Two times in one year
he tries to stop me.

491
00:39:24.783 --> 00:39:26.360
That's stretching coincidence. isn't it?

492
00:39:26.360 --> 00:39:28.680
What can I say?

493
00:39:28.680 --> 00:39:29.750
Don't say anything. Just listen.

494
00:39:29.750 --> 00:39:32.162
At least two guys are following us.

495
00:39:32.162 --> 00:39:34.361
One has an automatic weapon.
Maybe they both do.

496
00:39:34.361 --> 00:39:37.551
The helicopter was destroyed.
the pilot is dead.

497
00:39:37.551 --> 00:39:39.082
The perps are on the train.

498
00:39:39.082 --> 00:39:42.090
They don't know what the girl looks like.

499
00:39:42.090 --> 00:39:45.261
They sure as hell know what I look like.
I don't think we can stay on this train.

500
00:39:55.636 --> 00:39:56.810
Where the hell is this train?

501
00:39:57.241 --> 00:39:58.226
We're heading west towards Vancouver

502
00:39:58.591 --> 00:39:59.833
We'll be there at 10:00 a.m.

503
00:39:59.833 --> 00:40:02.415
We can't hold out. They'll find her.

504
00:40:02.415 --> 00:40:03.344
Where's the next stop?

505
00:40:04.192 --> 00:40:07.011
Uh. a town called Monashee.

506
00:40:07.379 --> 00:40:08.425
We'll be in there about midnight.

507
00:40:08.425 --> 00:40:12.144
Do what you can to keep the girl
hidden until then.

508
00:40:12.144 --> 00:40:13.297
I'll have you met at the next station.

509
00:40:13.597 --> 00:40:16.607
don't say anything to Larner about this.

510
00:40:16.632 --> 00:40:20.510
I won't. Hey. uh... You hang in there.

511
00:40:20.510 --> 00:40:21.343
Yeah. sure.

512
00:41:51.826 --> 00:41:52.978
He's gone.

513
00:41:57.171 --> 00:41:58.752
We're changing cars.

514
00:41:59.052 --> 00:42:00.840
This one is getting too popular.

515
00:42:05.605 --> 00:42:08.028
We get into the next station
around midnight.

516
00:42:08.028 --> 00:42:09.876
There'll be some people there to meet us.

517
00:42:13.237 --> 00:42:15.266
Then we can get off this damn train.

518
00:42:15.266 --> 00:42:16.786
Thank god.

519
00:42:24.768 --> 00:42:26.713
These guys can't just go blasting

520
00:42:26.713 --> 00:42:28.419
Everybody in sight.
They're professionals.

521
00:42:28.419 --> 00:42:31.352
They start a war on a train
in the boon-docks.

522
00:42:31.352 --> 00:42:33.300
they got a good chance of being caught.

523
00:42:36.538 --> 00:42:38.215
They have to find you. do it cleanly.

524
00:42:38.215 --> 00:42:40.790
without drawing attention to themselves.

525
00:42:40.790 --> 00:42:45.542
If they don't know where you are.
you're OK.

526
00:42:47.073 --> 00:42:48.844
It's going to be OK. really.

527
00:42:48.844 --> 00:42:51.502
I'm telling you.
it's going to be all right.

528
00:42:51.502 --> 00:42:54.029
I'm not going to Los Angeles with you.

529
00:42:54.029 --> 00:42:56.328
I'm telling you right now. I'm not going.

530
00:42:56.328 --> 00:42:58.582
- You hungry?
- Oh. I don't know.

531
00:42:58.582 --> 00:43:01.238
- I'll get you something.
- I'm not hungry.

532
00:43:01.238 --> 00:43:04.010
Lock this door.
Don't let the porter or the conductor ...

533
00:43:04.010 --> 00:43:05.673
I said I'm not hungry.

534
00:43:05.673 --> 00:43:08.993
- You need something to eat.
- OK. you stay. and I'll go.

535
00:43:08.993 --> 00:43:10.455
What?

536
00:43:10.455 --> 00:43:12.037
Every time you leave this compartment.

537
00:43:12.037 --> 00:43:15.234
And every time you come back.
you put me in danger.

538
00:43:15.234 --> 00:43:17.384
They know what you look like.

539
00:43:17.384 --> 00:43:20.296
They don't know me. I'll go myself.

540
00:43:20.296 --> 00:43:22.521
Suppose they do know what you look like?

541
00:43:22.521 --> 00:43:26.265
Maybe they've seen you.
Maybe your photograph was faxed

542
00:43:26.265 --> 00:43:28.798
when they checked you out.
Want to risk that?

543
00:43:28.798 --> 00:43:31.697
You don't want to bring me food.

544
00:43:31.697 --> 00:43:33.727
Lock the door behind me.

545
00:44:10.201 --> 00:44:12.400
- May I get you something to drink. sir?
- Yeah. a beer. please.

546
00:44:12.400 --> 00:44:15.324
- What kind?
- Oh. I don't know. You choose.

547
00:44:15.324 --> 00:44:16.218
Yes. sir.

548
00:44:19.468 --> 00:44:21.695
Oh!
I'm terribly sorry!

549
00:44:22.056 --> 00:44:24.750
- It's all right. It's OK
- Does it hurt?

550
00:44:24.750 --> 00:44:27.901
It's just my foot.
I'll grow another in a week.

551
00:44:27.901 --> 00:44:30.748
I'm so clumsy. I'm sorry.

552
00:44:30.748 --> 00:44:32.444
It's not you. it's the train.

553
00:44:32.444 --> 00:44:33.268
It's very bumpy. that's all.

554
00:44:33.268 --> 00:44:35.984
No. it's me.
I'm always doing things like that.

555
00:44:36.955 --> 00:44:39.525
Oh. I'm sorry again.

556
00:44:39.525 --> 00:44:41.566
It's OK. It's OK. It's the same foot.

557
00:44:42.574 --> 00:44:45.838
Gee!
Can I buy you something to drink?

558
00:44:45.838 --> 00:44:47.846
- No. that's not necessary.
- I'd like to.

559
00:44:47.846 --> 00:44:51.876
- I'm fine. really.
- I insist. I am clumsy. but I have money.

560
00:44:51.876 --> 00:44:53.562
I'm not that liberated yet.

561
00:44:54.452 --> 00:44:57.802
I'll have the same. please.
and this is for both of them.

562
00:44:58.562 --> 00:45:02.675
- Here. let me ... - No. no.
- It's done. Was it so difficult?

563
00:45:02.675 --> 00:45:04.228
I feel like Phil Donahue.

564
00:45:04.228 --> 00:45:08.591
My name's Kathryn Weller.

565
00:45:08.591 --> 00:45:10.893
I'm Robert Caulfield
How are you?

566
00:45:10.893 --> 00:45:11.812
Good.

567
00:45:13.862 --> 00:45:16.013
You don't look like somebody
who takes the train.

568
00:45:16.013 --> 00:45:20.098
What does somebody who takes
the train look like?

569
00:45:20.098 --> 00:45:21.735
Patient.

570
00:45:21.735 --> 00:45:23.906
Yeah. it's the first time I've done this.

571
00:45:23.906 --> 00:45:28.382
- No. that's fine.
- Thank you. ma'am.

572
00:45:29.570 --> 00:45:30.773
How about you? Do you do this often?

573
00:45:30.773 --> 00:45:33.685
No. not often. I. uh...

574
00:45:33.685 --> 00:45:35.965
I was trying to water-ski on Lake Louise.

575
00:45:35.965 --> 00:45:38.182
I wasn't good at it. I tend to fall down.

576
00:45:38.442 --> 00:45:39.565
I noticed.

577
00:45:42.047 --> 00:45:44.596
I'm also terrified of flying. so...

578
00:45:44.619 --> 00:45:46.476
Really? I don't mind that at all.

579
00:45:48.070 --> 00:45:49.532
I'm in no rush.

580
00:45:49.532 --> 00:45:51.474
The one thing I have is time.

581
00:45:53.893 --> 00:45:55.095
You also said you had money.

582
00:45:55.095 --> 00:45:58.658
Oh. I. uh ... I had a good divorce lawyer.

583
00:46:04.215 --> 00:46:04.907
Am I interrupting you?

584
00:46:04.907 --> 00:46:07.497
No. I'm sorry. really. I. uh...

585
00:46:07.497 --> 00:46:11.618
Well. here's to. uh ...
Community property.

586
00:46:13.034 --> 00:46:14.710
Come to think of it. I earned it.

587
00:46:18.225 --> 00:46:21.125
Are you ...
Are you travelling alone?

588
00:46:21.125 --> 00:46:22.942
- Yes.
- Oh.

589
00:46:24.472 --> 00:46:25.956
How long were you married?

590
00:46:25.956 --> 00:46:28.772
- Six years.
- Mm-hmm.

591
00:46:28.772 --> 00:46:32.523
One day over bran muffins ...
He loved bran muffins ...

592
00:46:32.523 --> 00:46:35.846
He said he had to find himself.
just like that.

593
00:46:35.846 --> 00:46:38.410
I'm standing there with
a pot of brewed decaf ...

594
00:46:38.410 --> 00:46:40.569
He only drank brewed decaf ...

595
00:46:40.569 --> 00:46:42.401
And he said he had to find himself.

596
00:46:42.401 --> 00:46:44.994
I asked if he wanted
to finish breakfast first.

597
00:46:44.994 --> 00:46:46.205
- Ha ha!
- Before I knew it.

598
00:46:46.205 --> 00:46:49.668
He'd taken his air popcorn maker ...
No cholesterol. you see ...

599
00:46:49.668 --> 00:46:53.208
And his life-cycle and moved
into this nice duplex

600
00:46:53.208 --> 00:46:55.509
With a 23-year-old waitress
from one of his restaurants.

601
00:46:55.509 --> 00:46:57.600
Not bad for somebody who's lost.

602
00:46:58.027 --> 00:47:01.365
He won't run out of waitresses.

603
00:47:01.365 --> 00:47:03.001
You'll have to excuse me.

604
00:47:04.247 --> 00:47:06.256
I'm sorry. I've been talking too much.

605
00:47:06.256 --> 00:47:07.823
- I tend to do it ...
- No. It's not you.

606
00:47:07.823 --> 00:47:08.440
I understand.

607
00:47:08.440 --> 00:47:11.902
I wish I could explain. but ...

608
00:47:11.902 --> 00:47:14.173
By the way.
I think your restaurant guy is nuts.

609
00:47:52.732 --> 00:47:54.537
I don't think this will work.

610
00:47:55.362 --> 00:47:57.382
I'll back up. It's shorter this way.

611
00:47:58.024 --> 00:47:59.491
- I appreciate that.
- These things weren't designed

612
00:47:59.491 --> 00:48:00.238
for people my size.

613
00:48:03.522 --> 00:48:06.405
No one loves a fat man but his grocer.

614
00:48:21.428 --> 00:48:23.620
Did you find your briefcase yet. sir?

615
00:48:23.620 --> 00:48:26.120
No. not yet.

616
00:48:26.120 --> 00:48:28.700
Aren't your seats
at the head of the train?

617
00:48:28.700 --> 00:48:31.518
That's right. I get mixed up.

618
00:48:31.518 --> 00:48:33.107
Well. it can be confusing. sir.

619
00:48:32.887 --> 00:48:34.206
Thank you.

620
00:48:48.661 --> 00:48:49.920
What the ...

621
00:48:49.920 --> 00:48:51.188
Shh! Shh!

622
00:48:55.446 --> 00:48:57.186
Please. I'm not going to hurt you.

623
00:49:00.991 --> 00:49:04.324
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

624
00:49:28.949 --> 00:49:31.133
You're supposed to say something.

625
00:49:31.133 --> 00:49:32.607
Like what?

626
00:49:33.740 --> 00:49:35.311
Something reassuring.

627
00:49:35.311 --> 00:49:36.663
It's going to work out.

628
00:49:38.278 --> 00:49:41.162
Thanks. That made a world of difference.

629
00:49:42.707 --> 00:49:44.918
We'll be in the station soon.

630
00:49:44.918 --> 00:49:47.333
You'll be safe when we get there.

631
00:49:49.186 --> 00:49:51.416
I hope they've gotten
to your cabin by now

632
00:49:51.416 --> 00:49:53.079
And taken care of Benti.

633
00:49:53.079 --> 00:49:55.252
He shouldn't be left alone like that.

634
00:49:56.368 --> 00:49:58.375
I'm sorry about your friend.

635
00:49:58.375 --> 00:49:59.733
He wasn't my friend.

636
00:50:02.887 --> 00:50:04.104
I just met him.

637
00:50:07.892 --> 00:50:08.862
The jerk.

638
00:50:08.862 --> 00:50:12.122
Two years away from retirement.

639
00:50:13.015 --> 00:50:14.672
I'm sorry.

640
00:50:14.818 --> 00:50:15.973
Are you?

641
00:50:15.973 --> 00:50:18.794
There are two guys on this train.

642
00:50:18.794 --> 00:50:21.267
One killed a police officer and a pilot.

643
00:50:21.267 --> 00:50:23.828
I couldn't see in the helicopter.
I couldn't identify them.

644
00:50:23.828 --> 00:50:26.262
You couldn't identify them.

645
00:50:26.262 --> 00:50:28.938
Except...

646
00:50:28.938 --> 00:50:30.715
They're the guys.

647
00:50:31.629 --> 00:50:33.134
They work for Leo Watts.

648
00:50:33.134 --> 00:50:35.318
There's nothing I can do.

649
00:50:35.318 --> 00:50:37.947
All I can charge him with
is riding on a train.

650
00:50:37.947 --> 00:50:39.203
They're going to walk.

651
00:50:42.274 --> 00:50:44.193
There'll be a funeral for Benti.

652
00:50:44.193 --> 00:50:46.938
Flag-draped coffin.

653
00:50:46.938 --> 00:50:48.671
Everybody in dress blues.

654
00:50:48.671 --> 00:50:50.516
His picture on the precinct wall.

655
00:50:50.516 --> 00:50:53.264
People saying how terrible it was.

656
00:50:55.486 --> 00:50:57.112
Not as spiffy as Benti's.

657
00:50:56.891 --> 00:50:58.186
No flags. nothing like that.

658
00:50:58.186 --> 00:51:02.674
There'll be two wives serving
a lot of food.

659
00:51:02.674 --> 00:51:05.310
Two groups of children trying
to be very brave.

660
00:51:05.310 --> 00:51:07.867
Those two guys died

661
00:51:07.867 --> 00:51:10.653
Trying to help get you back
to Los Angeles.

662
00:51:10.653 --> 00:51:11.986
And the two guys who killed them

663
00:51:11.986 --> 00:51:13.449
Are going to walk.

664
00:51:14.689 --> 00:51:18.066
Unless you testify against the man
who sent them up here.

665
00:51:25.150 --> 00:51:26.956
Two years from retirement.

666
00:51:32.025 --> 00:51:34.395
What a jerk.

667
00:51:51.886 --> 00:51:53.285
Keep the lights out.

668
00:52:06.421 --> 00:52:09.342
Jesus. they didn't exactly
bring out the national guard.

669
00:52:11.609 --> 00:52:14.270
I guess they didn't want to
attract too much attention.

670
00:52:14.270 --> 00:52:16.351
You stay here. OK?

671
00:52:18.001 --> 00:52:21.280
don't do anything.
but just stay out of sight.

672
00:52:21.280 --> 00:52:24.466
When we're ready.
when I think It's secure.

673
00:52:24.466 --> 00:52:26.352
I'll come and get you.

674
00:52:26.352 --> 00:52:28.454
Oh. and. uh...

675
00:52:28.454 --> 00:52:30.694
I know. I know. lock it.

676
00:52:49.023 --> 00:52:50.772
- You Caulfield?
- Yeah.

677
00:52:51.360 --> 00:52:52.856
I'm Sergeant Nigro. RCMP.

678
00:52:52.856 --> 00:52:54.531
This is Detective Loughlin.

679
00:52:56.218 --> 00:52:58.021
They sent two of you. huh?

680
00:52:58.021 --> 00:52:59.658
It's a pretty remote area.

681
00:52:59.658 --> 00:53:02.356
- Backup's on the way.
- So. you guys are mounties?

682
00:53:02.356 --> 00:53:06.358
Yes. uh. we don't really
use horses any more.

683
00:53:06.358 --> 00:53:07.984
That's mostly for the tourists.

684
00:53:07.984 --> 00:53:10.959
Besides. horses don't
have air conditioning.

685
00:53:13.362 --> 00:53:15.563
I don't think we should
stand around out here

686
00:53:15.563 --> 00:53:17.092
any longer than is necessary.

687
00:53:17.092 --> 00:53:18.186
Where's the woman?

688
00:53:18.221 --> 00:53:21.254
She's on the train. I've got her hidden.

689
00:53:22.337 --> 00:53:23.961
A couple guys on the train
have been following us.

690
00:53:23.961 --> 00:53:24.768
They're armed.

691
00:53:24.768 --> 00:53:27.550
I think I've got them on a possible 314.

692
00:53:27.550 --> 00:53:29.680
I think we can get the woman into safe custody.

693
00:53:29.921 --> 00:53:31.947
Your 314's can't get anywhere.

694
00:53:31.947 --> 00:53:34.461
We'll send units to meet
the train at the next stop.

695
00:53:34.692 --> 00:53:36.035
We'll nail them.

696
00:53:36.227 --> 00:53:38.529
I think you're right.

697
00:53:38.721 --> 00:53:39.758
Why don't you get the woman

698
00:53:39.949 --> 00:53:40.986
And we can get out of here?

699
00:53:44.501 --> 00:53:46.693
Listen. I know you'll think
this is dumb of me.

700
00:53:46.693 --> 00:53:48.720
but I haven't been feeling good lately.

701
00:53:48.720 --> 00:53:50.493
My stomach. you know.

702
00:53:50.493 --> 00:53:52.954
So I got to run over to the toilet

703
00:53:52.954 --> 00:53:55.566
- for a second.
- Are you serious?

704
00:53:55.566 --> 00:53:58.362
I don't have any choice.
You know what it's like.

705
00:53:58.362 --> 00:53:59.180
I'll be right back.

706
00:55:14.593 --> 00:55:17.121
Mr. Caulfield. you all right?

707
00:55:19.323 --> 00:55:20.158
Caulfield?

708
00:55:48.064 --> 00:55:49.224
Shithead.

709
00:55:49.224 --> 00:55:51.886
A 314 is indecent exposure.
You're no cop.

710
00:55:51.886 --> 00:55:53.220
- Who sent you?
- Fuck you.

711
00:56:16.858 --> 00:56:19.985
You're a dead man. do you know that?

712
01:00:30.450 --> 01:00:33.850
- You all right. sir?
- Yeah. That was close.

713
01:00:33.850 --> 01:00:38.208
I was taking a walk.
I didn't realize the train was leaving.

714
01:00:38.208 --> 01:00:39.089
You could have been hurt.

715
01:00:39.089 --> 01:00:41.553
That was stupid of me.

716
01:00:41.553 --> 01:00:42.995
I'll never do that again.

717
01:00:43.030 --> 01:00:44.180
I certainly hope not.

718
01:00:44.175 --> 01:00:47.118
Listen ...

719
01:00:47.942 --> 01:00:48.920
Never mind.

720
01:01:40.251 --> 01:01:43.462
Mr. Caulfield.
I have a business proposition

721
01:01:43.462 --> 01:01:45.270
that might interest you.

722
01:01:45.462 --> 01:01:49.045
Would you care for a drink?
What will you have? It's my treat.

723
01:01:49.045 --> 01:01:52.435
Coffee. please.
Seven and seven for me.

724
01:01:52.435 --> 01:01:54.122
And scotch for my associate.

725
01:01:54.931 --> 01:01:56.781
I figured him for something
with an umbrella in it.

726
01:01:56.781 --> 01:01:59.099
He won't lose his composure.

727
01:01:59.099 --> 01:02:00.950
He's very good at what he does.

728
01:02:00.950 --> 01:02:01.877
So am I

729
01:02:01.877 --> 01:02:05.439
But I do it for a living. He enjoys it.

730
01:02:05.439 --> 01:02:07.615
People should have fun at work.

731
01:02:07.615 --> 01:02:09.220
It makes the day go by quicker.

732
01:02:09.220 --> 01:02:14.196
As I said.
I have a business proposition for you.

733
01:02:14.196 --> 01:02:16.146
Tell me.

734
01:02:16.146 --> 01:02:19.673
how much does a deputy district attorney

735
01:02:19.673 --> 01:02:21.026
make in a year?

736
01:02:21.026 --> 01:02:23.429
- Enough.
- Oh. I doubt that.

737
01:02:23.429 --> 01:02:25.406
Are you thinking of becoming a lawyer?

738
01:02:25.406 --> 01:02:28.622
I was thinking we might
negotiate an arrangement

739
01:02:28.622 --> 01:02:30.288
That would be mutually satisfactory.

740
01:02:30.288 --> 01:02:33.512
He says he thinks we can make a deal.

741
01:02:33.512 --> 01:02:34.987
Ha ha ha.

742
01:02:34.987 --> 01:02:37.536
Does he speak?

743
01:02:37.536 --> 01:02:40.704
Yeah. Sometimes very convincingly.

744
01:02:40.704 --> 01:02:42.488
I'm going to enjoy this.

745
01:02:44.313 --> 01:02:46.490
- Thank you. Keep the change.
- Thank you. sir.

746
01:02:49.629 --> 01:02:52.371
The people I work for
are very determined.

747
01:02:52.371 --> 01:02:53.207
They want the woman.

748
01:02:53.207 --> 01:02:55.759
You have her.

749
01:02:55.759 --> 01:02:57.181
and the question is simply.

750
01:02:57.181 --> 01:02:59.308
how much do you want?

751
01:02:59.308 --> 01:03:01.027
What woman?

752
01:03:01.027 --> 01:03:04.552
Well. you know we're going to find her.

753
01:03:04.552 --> 01:03:05.392
It's just a matter of time.

754
01:03:05.392 --> 01:03:06.646
What I'm proposing here

755
01:03:06.646 --> 01:03:08.738
is that you recognize the inevitable.

756
01:03:08.738 --> 01:03:12.096
I don't know what woman
You're talking about.

757
01:03:12.096 --> 01:03:13.409
First you lost your briefcase.

758
01:03:13.409 --> 01:03:15.332
And now you've lost some woman.

759
01:03:15.332 --> 01:03:17.474
You ought to be more careful.

760
01:03:17.474 --> 01:03:21.954
The people I work for
have a large investment in this matter.

761
01:03:21.954 --> 01:03:24.889
and they are very determined.

762
01:03:24.889 --> 01:03:27.823
- They sound like interesting people.
- Very interesting.

763
01:03:27.823 --> 01:03:28.834
You have a good dental plan?

764
01:03:28.834 --> 01:03:31.495
What I'm talking about

765
01:03:31.495 --> 01:03:35.683
is probably 10 times
what you earn in a year.

766
01:03:35.683 --> 01:03:37.600
including whatever you
steal on your expense account.

767
01:03:37.600 --> 01:03:40.213
- I don't steal.
- An honest man. I like that.

768
01:03:40.213 --> 01:03:42.716
- So do I.
- 10 times.

769
01:03:42.716 --> 01:03:45.669
You could never make that much
if you worked another 30 years.

770
01:03:45.669 --> 01:03:49.271
And then there's always the possibility you
won't survive that long.

771
01:03:49.271 --> 01:03:50.395
That's true.

772
01:03:53.038 --> 01:03:55.555
All you have to do is point her out

773
01:03:55.555 --> 01:03:58.747
and look the other way.
Now. that's not a great deal of effort

774
01:03:58.747 --> 01:04:00.316
for more money than you ever dreamed of.

775
01:04:00.316 --> 01:04:03.239
And no risk to you at all.

776
01:04:03.239 --> 01:04:05.542
You go through the motions
of guarding her.

777
01:04:05.542 --> 01:04:06.947
We'll take care of the rest.

778
01:04:06.947 --> 01:04:09.556
This offer doesn't stay
on the table too long.

779
01:04:09.556 --> 01:04:14.527
There are a few things to know
before making your decision.

780
01:04:14.527 --> 01:04:17.838
Jack. show him what you have.

781
01:04:21.753 --> 01:04:23.093
Do you know what this is?

782
01:04:23.093 --> 01:04:25.541
I have a feeling you're going to tell me.

783
01:04:25.541 --> 01:04:28.801
Something's happened to the
communications gear on this train

784
01:04:28.801 --> 01:04:31.394
There's no way for anyone to radio ahead.

785
01:04:31.394 --> 01:04:33.073
That's a shame. isn't it?

786
01:04:33.073 --> 01:04:35.027
The other item that might
interest you

787
01:04:35.027 --> 01:04:36.683
is that when this train
reaches its destination.

788
01:04:36.683 --> 01:04:39.188
some people will be waiting for you.

789
01:04:39.188 --> 01:04:41.287
Quite a few of them.
They're not like us.

790
01:04:41.287 --> 01:04:44.873
Now. we have no desire
for needless violence.

791
01:04:44.873 --> 01:04:47.552
We're professionals. like you.

792
01:04:47.552 --> 01:04:49.645
To have an ugly incident occur on this train

793
01:04:49.645 --> 01:04:50.830
with no method of escape

794
01:04:50.830 --> 01:04:52.909
isn't in our self-interest. either.

795
01:04:52.909 --> 01:04:55.841
However. the men waiting for you.

796
01:04:55.841 --> 01:04:59.325
that's a different matter.

797
01:04:59.325 --> 01:05:01.352
They simply won't let you and that woman

798
01:05:01.387 --> 01:05:02.096
Get off this train and walk away.
It's that simple.

799
01:05:02.096 --> 01:05:03.951
I've been doing some checking on you.

800
01:05:03.951 --> 01:05:06.236
You have an interesting resume.

801
01:05:06.271 --> 01:05:09.400
Top of your law school class.
A decorated marine.

802
01:05:09.488 --> 01:05:13.223
And you have a reputation
for being a very good prosecutor.

803
01:05:13.223 --> 01:05:17.018
You also have a reputation
for having something of a big mouth.

804
01:05:17.018 --> 01:05:18.937
It seems you pissed off too many people.

805
01:05:18.937 --> 01:05:21.234
You're never going to be the district attorney.

806
01:05:21.234 --> 01:05:22.629
It's a shame. isn't it?

807
01:05:22.629 --> 01:05:24.473
I suppose there's two reasons

808
01:05:24.473 --> 01:05:26.968
why someone would remain
a deputy district attorney.

809
01:05:26.968 --> 01:05:29.220
You're either rich or afraid to
go out on your own.

810
01:05:29.220 --> 01:05:31.327
There's a third reason.

811
01:05:31.327 --> 01:05:34.230
I don't like people like you.

812
01:05:34.230 --> 01:05:36.809
And I really don't like people
like your boss.

813
01:05:36.809 --> 01:05:39.285
I enjoy putting you away. I really do.

814
01:05:39.285 --> 01:05:42.641
If I wanted to make money.
I'd have to defend you.

815
01:05:42.641 --> 01:05:46.125
That wouldn't be any fun.
I'd always feel like showering.

816
01:05:46.125 --> 01:05:47.758
I enjoy sitting in a courtroom.

817
01:05:47.758 --> 01:05:48.908
Watching the judge pass sentence.

818
01:05:48.908 --> 01:05:52.644
As your shirt collar
starts to get a little tight.

819
01:05:52.644 --> 01:05:56.502
I'll love sitting there watching Leo Watts.

820
01:05:56.502 --> 01:05:58.407
I like my courtroom side.

821
01:05:58.407 --> 01:06:00.737
Pay's not so good. but the air's a lot better.

822
01:06:00.737 --> 01:06:04.515
I'm offering you enough money
to make your whole life different.

823
01:06:04.515 --> 01:06:07.303
don't tell me that
you're above temptation.

824
01:06:07.303 --> 01:06:10.527
I'm very tempted at your offer. yes.

825
01:06:10.527 --> 01:06:13.019
- There's just one small problem.
- What's that?

826
01:06:13.019 --> 01:06:16.392
I don't know who this woman is
you keep talking about.

827
01:06:16.392 --> 01:06:19.504
I'll really enjoy this.

828
01:06:19.504 --> 01:06:20.443
Give it a rest. will you?

829
01:06:22.009 --> 01:06:24.615
There are no more stops
between here and Vancouver

830
01:06:24.615 --> 01:06:27.579
Neither of you can get off the train.

831
01:06:27.949 --> 01:06:29.369
You don't have a lot of choice.

832
01:06:29.369 --> 01:06:31.226
Think about it.

833
01:06:31.835 --> 01:06:32.909
I will.

834
01:06:32.949 --> 01:06:35.269
Do you really think
you can get her off this train?

835
01:06:35.269 --> 01:06:36.534
Get who?

836
01:06:40.986 --> 01:06:42.161
Well. uh...

837
01:06:42.161 --> 01:06:45.631
- Thank you for the coffee.
- Uh-huh.

838
01:06:48.040 --> 01:06:50.692
I've really enjoyed this little chat.
I really have.

839
01:06:50.692 --> 01:06:53.250
- I must go now.
- We'll talk again.

840
01:06:53.250 --> 01:06:55.482
Yeah. well ... I'm in the book.

841
01:07:12.261 --> 01:07:13.180
It's me.

842
01:07:16.743 --> 01:07:18.551
Jesus Christ. what happened?

843
01:07:20.587 --> 01:07:24.360
Your friend Leo Watts has
a buddy in the D.A.'s office.

844
01:07:24.360 --> 01:07:25.421
His name is Dahlbeck.

845
01:07:25.421 --> 01:07:27.774
Those two guys he sent here.
they weren't cops.

846
01:07:27.774 --> 01:07:30.193
- I thought you were dead.
- Well. I'm not.

847
01:07:30.789 --> 01:07:33.809
When I get to L.A.. Dahlbeck is mine.

848
01:07:33.759 --> 01:07:36.812
- If you get there.
- We'll get there. I'll take care of it.

849
01:07:36.812 --> 01:07:38.888
Are you telling me not to worry

850
01:07:38.888 --> 01:07:40.791
while you work everything out?

851
01:07:40.791 --> 01:07:43.495
This is my life we're dealing with.

852
01:07:43.495 --> 01:07:46.905
I thought you were dead

853
01:07:46.905 --> 01:07:50.063
And I was on my own.
You prance in here with your fancy I.D.

854
01:07:50.063 --> 01:07:51.459
And tell me not to worry?

855
01:07:51.459 --> 01:07:53.136
You're really a jerk.

856
01:07:55.620 --> 01:07:57.626
My friend Leo Watts?

857
01:07:57.626 --> 01:08:00.029
Do you know what really happened?

858
01:08:00.029 --> 01:08:02.311
I mean. do you know anything about me?

859
01:08:02.311 --> 01:08:04.157
I know you're Michael Tarlow's
girlfriend.

860
01:08:06.963 --> 01:08:07.983
It must be really nice

861
01:08:07.983 --> 01:08:10.404
not to let knowledge get in your way.

862
01:08:15.764 --> 01:08:18.168
I never met Michael Tarlow in my life

863
01:08:18.168 --> 01:08:19.150
before that night.

864
01:08:20.795 --> 01:08:23.221
I was fixed up on a blind date

865
01:08:23.221 --> 01:08:24.837
By a well-meaning friend.

866
01:08:27.078 --> 01:08:28.722
I saw a man get murdered.

867
01:08:28.722 --> 01:08:32.312
I don't know if he was good or bad.

868
01:08:32.312 --> 01:08:34.989
I saw someone take his life

869
01:08:34.989 --> 01:08:37.183
as casually as you'd buy a stick of gum.

870
01:08:38.649 --> 01:08:42.526
It's not like it is on television.
It was horrible.

871
01:08:42.526 --> 01:08:43.795
It's not a part of my life.

872
01:08:43.795 --> 01:08:46.604
It's something you read about.

873
01:08:46.604 --> 01:08:48.662
except that it never happens to you.

874
01:08:48.662 --> 01:08:52.220
Ohh ...

875
01:08:52.220 --> 01:08:55.686
I don't know how I got home that night.

876
01:08:55.686 --> 01:08:57.928
The most difficult part was acting normal

877
01:08:57.928 --> 01:08:59.681
when I paid the babysitter.

878
01:08:59.681 --> 01:09:04.101
Yes. I have a son.

879
01:09:04.101 --> 01:09:05.655
He's 10 years old.

880
01:09:05.655 --> 01:09:07.249
But I thought you would have known that.

881
01:09:07.249 --> 01:09:09.031
since you know everything about me.

882
01:09:09.031 --> 01:09:13.474
I just went into his room that night
and watched him sleeping.

883
01:09:13.474 --> 01:09:16.427
Thought maybe the sight of
that kind of innocence

884
01:09:16.427 --> 01:09:18.908
would make the world seem less horrible.

885
01:09:18.908 --> 01:09:19.649
It didn't.

886
01:09:19.649 --> 01:09:21.808
It was all over the 11:00 news

887
01:09:21.808 --> 01:09:23.734
who Michael Tarlow was.

888
01:09:23.734 --> 01:09:25.462
That he was a lawyer

889
01:09:25.462 --> 01:09:29.352
for this... famous gangster
named Leo Watts.

890
01:09:29.352 --> 01:09:32.305
They had a photograph of Leo Watts on television.

891
01:09:32.305 --> 01:09:34.001
That was the man in the hotel room.

892
01:09:34.001 --> 01:09:35.896
All I could think of was to run.

893
01:09:37.972 --> 01:09:40.490
I took my son to his father's house.

894
01:09:40.490 --> 01:09:42.797
I told his father to go away right then.

895
01:09:42.797 --> 01:09:45.398
Not to tell anybody where he was going.

896
01:09:45.398 --> 01:09:46.524
Not even me.

897
01:09:46.524 --> 01:09:50.940
I knew I had to get
as far away from my son as I could.

898
01:09:50.940 --> 01:09:54.391
I went to my brother's cabin.

899
01:09:54.391 --> 01:09:57.542
It's so remote I thought
I'd be safe there.

900
01:09:57.542 --> 01:09:59.017
I figured no one could find me.

901
01:09:59.017 --> 01:10:00.922
So don't you ever judge me.

902
01:10:01.222 --> 01:10:03.831
don't you dare.

903
01:10:04.023 --> 01:10:08.322
I'm scared stiff.

904
01:10:09.051 --> 01:10:13.349
I don't want to die.

905
01:10:14.270 --> 01:10:17.571
I'd gladly die for my son. however.

906
01:10:17.762 --> 01:10:21.140
This is not just about me.

907
01:10:21.332 --> 01:10:23.980
I would like to do the right thing.

908
01:10:24.171 --> 01:10:26.512
I really would. I just ...

909
01:10:26.666 --> 01:10:28.969
I'm just so scared.

910
01:10:29.161 --> 01:10:33.459
This is not just about me.

911
01:10:36.068 --> 01:10:37.872
So here's the program.

912
01:10:38.064 --> 01:10:39.868
You're going to tell me what's going on.

913
01:10:39.983 --> 01:10:42.900
and you'll tell me your ideas
if you have any.

914
01:10:43.092 --> 01:10:47.390
I need to know.

915
01:10:48.119 --> 01:10:51.304
I'm sorry.

916
01:10:51.535 --> 01:10:54.336
They still don't know where you are.

917
01:10:54.528 --> 01:10:56.025
I don't think they'll move tonight

918
01:10:56.255 --> 01:10:57.330
Because they don't have to.

919
01:10:57.521 --> 01:10:58.404
We have to do something

920
01:10:58.596 --> 01:11:02.626
before this train makes the last stop. though.

921
01:11:02.818 --> 01:11:05.619
We can't get off the train.

922
01:11:05.849 --> 01:11:09.994
There isn't anybody I can call for help.

923
01:11:10.186 --> 01:11:12.949
They've got somebody else on the train

924
01:11:13.141 --> 01:11:14.599
besides the two guys.

925
01:11:14.791 --> 01:11:19.051
I think I know who it is ...
a big. fat guy.

926
01:11:19.473 --> 01:11:21.469
I. uh...

927
01:11:21.661 --> 01:11:25.537
I don't know exactly
what I'm going to do.

928
01:11:25.729 --> 01:11:27.533
I just know that I've ...

929
01:11:27.724 --> 01:11:31.984
I have to make my move
before they make theirs.

930
01:11:32.752 --> 01:11:33.481
Why don't you try to get some sleep now?

931
01:11:33.711 --> 01:11:36.820
You're going to need it.

932
01:11:37.012 --> 01:11:38.739
I can't sleep.

933
01:11:38.931 --> 01:11:43.191
Don't worry. I'll be up.

934
01:11:47.335 --> 01:11:51.058
You should wash that.

935
01:11:51.250 --> 01:11:55.548
Thank you.

936
01:12:25.291 --> 01:12:26.442
Ooh. Oh...

937
01:12:26.595 --> 01:12:29.435
It's OK
Nothing's happened.

938
01:12:29.627 --> 01:12:31.508
OK? We're not dead yet?

939
01:12:31.700 --> 01:12:35.269
No... we're not dead yet.

940
01:12:35.461 --> 01:12:37.226
Well. that's good.

941
01:12:37.418 --> 01:12:39.989
I'm leaving you alone for a little while.

942
01:12:40.181 --> 01:12:42.484
- Where are you going?
- To the dining car.

943
01:12:42.714 --> 01:12:44.441
There they can't get by me

944
01:12:44.633 --> 01:12:47.089
without my seeing them first.

945
01:12:47.319 --> 01:12:51.579
If they come after me.
at least you won't be right next to me.

946
01:12:59.523 --> 01:13:01.135
You'll be all right.

947
01:13:01.327 --> 01:13:04.320
Would you like some coffee?

948
01:13:04.512 --> 01:13:06.009
That would be nice.

949
01:13:25.428 --> 01:13:27.961
Freeze. mister.
You're not robbing this train.

950
01:13:28.153 --> 01:13:30.187
Jesus Christ

951
01:13:30.379 --> 01:13:31.530
That thing's not for real. is it?

952
01:13:31.760 --> 01:13:35.752
- Course not. I'm a kid.
- You could get hurt pointing that thing.

953
01:13:35.943 --> 01:13:38.400
If you around robbing people you could go to jail.

954
01:13:38.591 --> 01:13:40.894
- I'm not a robber.
- I don't believe you.

955
01:13:41.086 --> 01:13:42.621
Now. uh...

956
01:13:42.813 --> 01:13:43.964
Listen. I got to go.

957
01:13:44.156 --> 01:13:45.590
I didn't say you could move.

958
01:13:46.996 --> 01:13:49.913
- Well. I got to go.
- I'll be watching you.

959
01:13:50.105 --> 01:13:50.719
What's your name?

960
01:13:50.911 --> 01:13:53.520
Nick.

961
01:13:53.751 --> 01:13:55.055
Do you always go around
pretending you're a cop?

962
01:13:55.247 --> 01:13:56.744
Sometimes I'm the bad guy.

963
01:13:56.936 --> 01:13:59.123
I understand. It pays better. right?

964
01:13:59.354 --> 01:14:02.347
But now you're a cop.

965
01:14:02.539 --> 01:14:06.799
- Can you keep a secret?
- Of course I can.

966
01:14:14.628 --> 01:14:17.506
Suppose I told you I was really a cop.

967
01:14:17.736 --> 01:14:20.960
- No way.
- Suppose I could prove it to you.

968
01:14:21.152 --> 01:14:23.378
Suppose I asked you for your help.

969
01:14:23.570 --> 01:14:24.491
Would you give it to me.

970
01:14:24.683 --> 01:14:27.561
Without telling anybody.
not saying anything to anyone?

971
01:14:27.753 --> 01:14:28.804
Prove it.

972
01:14:33.701 --> 01:14:35.237
- Is that real?
- Yes. it is.

973
01:14:35.467 --> 01:14:36.964
No shit.

974
01:14:37.194 --> 01:14:40.264
This doesn't say you're a cop.
I can read you know.

975
01:14:40.456 --> 01:14:41.530
Doesn't it say deputy?

976
01:14:41.722 --> 01:14:43.795
- Are you on a case?
- Big one.

977
01:14:43.987 --> 01:14:45.752
Where's your gun?

978
01:14:45.944 --> 01:14:47.018
I don't have it.

979
01:14:47.210 --> 01:14:49.513
If you're a real cop.
how come you don't have a gun?

980
01:14:49.743 --> 01:14:52.046
That's the problem.
The bad guys took it.

981
01:14:52.238 --> 01:14:55.692
- Are you kidding me?
- No. I need your help.

982
01:14:55.922 --> 01:14:56.843
You do?

983
01:14:57.073 --> 01:14:58.417
I need to borrow your gun.

984
01:14:58.608 --> 01:14:59.491
But it's not real.

985
01:14:59.683 --> 01:15:02.101
Well. we won't tell
anybody about that. OK?

986
01:15:02.293 --> 01:15:04.212
Raise your right hand.

987
01:15:04.403 --> 01:15:06.361
Put your left hand on the gun.

988
01:15:06.553 --> 01:15:07.819
I'm going to deputize you.

989
01:15:08.011 --> 01:15:09.738
According to California state laws

990
01:15:09.930 --> 01:15:12.117
And international laws of criminal justice.

991
01:15:12.309 --> 01:15:15.610
I hereby deputize you as special assistant...

992
01:15:15.802 --> 01:15:18.641
Uh. subject to all the laws of. uh...

993
01:15:18.833 --> 01:15:21.904
Secrecy and jurisprudence. 
so help me God. Say ''I do.''

994
01:15:22.095 --> 01:15:23.746
I do. What does it mean?

995
01:15:23.938 --> 01:15:25.665
It means. um...

996
01:15:25.856 --> 01:15:27.468
If you say anything about this.

997
01:15:27.660 --> 01:15:29.848
- your ass is grass.
- OK

998
01:15:30.040 --> 01:15:33.340
OK. deputy.
Go see your mother now. Just act normal.

999
01:15:33.532 --> 01:15:37.792
Yes. sir.

1000
01:15:42.128 --> 01:15:43.664
Good morning. sir.
Would you like some breakfast?

1001
01:15:43.855 --> 01:15:46.734
Uh. no. thanks. Just some coffee.
please. Black.

1002
01:15:46.926 --> 01:15:51.224
- And a cup of coffee to go.
- Certainly. sir.

1003
01:15:53.373 --> 01:15:55.177
Well. Good morning.

1004
01:15:55.369 --> 01:15:56.482
Good morning.

1005
01:15:56.712 --> 01:15:58.017
Mind if I join you?

1006
01:15:58.209 --> 01:16:00.434
I'm just having coffee.
I'm not having breakfast.

1007
01:16:00.626 --> 01:16:02.277
Um... oh. of course.

1008
01:16:02.392 --> 01:16:06.690
- Please. Sit down.
- Thank you.

1009
01:16:11.334 --> 01:16:12.945
- Sleep well?
- Not much.

1010
01:16:13.137 --> 01:16:14.481
Me. too.

1011
01:16:14.672 --> 01:16:17.704
It's so difficult to sleep on a train.

1012
01:16:17.896 --> 01:16:20.544
- God. it's beautiful. isn't it?
- Yes. yes.

1013
01:16:20.736 --> 01:16:22.962
Good morning. ma'am.
Would you care for some breakfast?

1014
01:16:23.154 --> 01:16:25.879
Um. just some tea. please.
And some toast.

1015
01:16:26.071 --> 01:16:27.184
What kind of bread?

1016
01:16:27.414 --> 01:16:31.674
Any kind. Wheat?

1017
01:16:32.326 --> 01:16:34.552
You. um. getting coffee for someone?

1018
01:16:34.744 --> 01:16:36.471
No. I thought I'd have a cup here

1019
01:16:36.701 --> 01:16:38.774
And take a cup back to the compartment.

1020
01:16:38.965 --> 01:16:42.381
I have reading to do before we get in.

1021
01:16:42.573 --> 01:16:44.070
What kind of work do you do?

1022
01:16:44.261 --> 01:16:47.485
Mmm. Sales.

1023
01:16:47.677 --> 01:16:49.442
What do you sell?

1024
01:16:49.634 --> 01:16:51.323
Construction. um ... supplies.

1025
01:16:51.553 --> 01:16:53.088
H-heavy equipment.

1026
01:16:53.280 --> 01:16:57.879
Oh. I see.
You don't look like the salesman type.

1027
01:16:58.269 --> 01:16:59.996
What type is that?

1028
01:17:00.188 --> 01:17:01.521
Well. somebody who looks comfortable

1029
01:17:01.556 --> 01:17:02.951
with a name tag on their pocket.

1030
01:17:03.143 --> 01:17:06.597
- ''Hello. my name is...''
- Yes. I don't have to do that.

1031
01:17:06.789 --> 01:17:11.087
- Your toast is coming.
- Thanks.

1032
01:17:12.546 --> 01:17:15.079
- Where are you from?
- Uh. Los Angeles.

1033
01:17:15.309 --> 01:17:17.535
Oh. I go there quite often.

1034
01:17:17.727 --> 01:17:21.027
In fact. I'm going to be there
next week.

1035
01:17:21.257 --> 01:17:24.136
I stay at the. um. the Bel Air.

1036
01:17:24.366 --> 01:17:27.666
That's a very nice place.

1037
01:17:27.858 --> 01:17:29.931
Would you like to see me?

1038
01:17:30.122 --> 01:17:31.235
What did you say? I'm sorry.

1039
01:17:31.427 --> 01:17:34.958
- Nothing. It's not important.
- No. what did you say?

1040
01:17:35.150 --> 01:17:36.301
I feel like an idiot.

1041
01:17:36.493 --> 01:17:40.177
I asked if you'd like to see me again.

1042
01:17:40.369 --> 01:17:42.019
How's she doing?
Your wife.

1043
01:17:42.211 --> 01:17:43.593
How's she doing?

1044
01:17:43.785 --> 01:17:46.356
I gave him my compartment.
He only had coach seats.

1045
01:17:46.548 --> 01:17:50.271
His wife looked like she was going to have
the baby right there in the train station.

1046
01:17:50.463 --> 01:17:52.190
She's doing fine. thank you.

1047
01:17:52.381 --> 01:17:53.916
That's very kind of you.

1048
01:17:54.108 --> 01:17:56.181
I hope you and your wife
were not uncomfortable.

1049
01:17:56.411 --> 01:17:58.599
Hell. no. We played cards all night.

1050
01:17:58.790 --> 01:18:01.170
I cheat. So does she. But I cheat better.

1051
01:18:01.400 --> 01:18:04.701
That's why she's buying breakfast.

1052
01:18:04.892 --> 01:18:06.658
Well. I got to be going.

1053
01:18:06.850 --> 01:18:08.155
Hope everything turns out right.

1054
01:18:08.346 --> 01:18:10.265
Thank you. You don't understand.

1055
01:18:10.496 --> 01:18:11.612
- I do understand.
- Please.

1056
01:18:11.612 --> 01:18:13.673
Look. you don't have to apologize.

1057
01:18:13.673 --> 01:18:17.604
No. please. I just ...
I can't explain. Please.

1058
01:18:21.548 --> 01:18:23.467
- Come with me.
- What?

1059
01:18:23.659 --> 01:18:25.224
Come with me now.
Don't ask questions.

1060
01:18:25.259 --> 01:18:25.616
I don't want to.

1061
01:18:25.808 --> 01:18:29.017
I'm not asking. I'm telling.
You're in danger.

1062
01:18:29.492 --> 01:18:30.701
What's going on here?

1063
01:18:31.411 --> 01:18:32.375
What is it?

1064
01:18:34.443 --> 01:18:35.982
Ow!

1065
01:18:36.784 --> 01:18:39.321
Where are you taking me? Who are you?

1066
01:18:39.321 --> 01:18:40.741
Those two guys think you're someone else.

1067
01:18:40.741 --> 01:18:42.232
Let go of me!

1068
01:18:42.232 --> 01:18:44.759
Get in your compartment. shut the door and lock it.

1069
01:18:44.759 --> 01:18:47.031
My compartment's back the other way.

1070
01:18:47.223 --> 01:18:48.144
You can't go back the other way.

1071
01:18:48.336 --> 01:18:50.610
Tell me what's going on.

1072
01:18:51.022 --> 01:18:52.630
I don't have time.

1073
01:18:55.781 --> 01:18:56.664
What's the problem here?

1074
01:18:56.855 --> 01:18:59.040
- This man ... - No problem.
- Looks like there's one to me.

1075
01:18:59.350 --> 01:19:01.101
I don't give a shit what it looks like to you.

1076
01:19:01.136 --> 01:19:02.093
No way to talk.

1077
01:19:02.093 --> 01:19:06.028
Come with me. The name's Keller.
Rail-road security.

1078
01:19:06.220 --> 01:19:07.640
Step away from the lady
and come with me.

1079
01:19:07.831 --> 01:19:08.829
You're a rail-road cop?

1080
01:19:09.021 --> 01:19:11.899
Two men on this train are trying
to kill someone.

1081
01:19:12.091 --> 01:19:13.818
The person they're after is a woman.

1082
01:19:14.010 --> 01:19:15.729
I know who the two are.
I've been watching them.

1083
01:19:15.764 --> 01:19:17.712
I've been watching you too.
Where is she?

1084
01:19:17.712 --> 01:19:20.765
She's safe. I believe they think
she's the woman.

1085
01:19:20.765 --> 01:19:22.645
What do you want me to do?
Where's your compartment?

1086
01:19:22.921 --> 01:19:24.905
- One car behind us.
- Let's go there.

1087
01:19:30.973 --> 01:19:33.084
Keep her in there.
They won't think to look there.

1088
01:19:33.276 --> 01:19:35.617
I can call ahead for help.

1089
01:19:35.809 --> 01:19:36.922
Communications aren't out?

1090
01:19:37.113 --> 01:19:38.917
- Mine's a portable.
- Have your people contact

1091
01:19:39.147 --> 01:19:41.028
The Los Angeles District
Attorney's office.

1092
01:19:41.181 --> 01:19:44.328
Have them ask for Chief Deputy District
Attorney Martin Larner.

1093
01:19:44.520 --> 01:19:46.708
They're not to talk to anyone else.
that's important.

1094
01:19:46.900 --> 01:19:50.392
I want them to tell Larner that
Dahlbeck is dirty.

1095
01:19:50.584 --> 01:19:51.735
Do it right away.

1096
01:19:51.927 --> 01:19:54.968
Listen. It's not just your grocer
who loves you.

1097
01:19:58.221 --> 01:19:59.748
It's Caulfield.

1098
01:20:00.485 --> 01:20:02.686
What took you so long?

1099
01:20:03.325 --> 01:20:04.996
We're going to change compartments. OK?

1100
01:20:09.964 --> 01:20:12.382
- What happened?
- Things are looking up.

1101
01:20:12.574 --> 01:20:15.491
I'm going to put you in a rail-road
cop's compartment.

1102
01:20:15.606 --> 01:20:17.537
If nothing else. it'll give us
a little time.

1103
01:20:24.893 --> 01:20:26.121
Jesus Christ

1104
01:20:26.236 --> 01:20:29.115
Oh!

1105
01:20:29.499 --> 01:20:31.574
- They took her.
- Who?

1106
01:20:32.185 --> 01:20:33.797
There was a woman in here.

1107
01:20:33.950 --> 01:20:36.957
They thought she was you.
Oh. dear god.

1108
01:20:37.596 --> 01:20:38.956
Oh!

1109
01:20:49.762 --> 01:20:50.180
Get out of the way!

1110
01:21:00.968 --> 01:21:01.892
Wait!

1111
01:21:17.163 --> 01:21:18.567
- Get on the roof!.
- I can't!

1112
01:21:18.660 --> 01:21:19.717
You don't have any choice.

1113
01:21:19.717 --> 01:21:21.570
Don't think about it.
Just do it.

1114
01:21:28.561 --> 01:21:30.971
When you get on the roof. lie flat!

1115
01:21:34.088 --> 01:21:34.890
You're doing fine!

1116
01:22:23.595 --> 01:22:26.435
End of the line. asshole.

1117
01:22:26.626 --> 01:22:28.584
Wiggle your ears. Wiggle your toes.

1118
01:22:28.814 --> 01:22:30.501
Come on. I want to do you.

1119
01:22:34.532 --> 01:22:36.587
Toy gun.
Ha ha ha ha!

1120
01:23:22.120 --> 01:23:24.985
- Let's go!
- I can't move! I'm afraid!

1121
01:23:25.689 --> 01:23:27.685
- Yeah. so am I. Let's go. Come on.
- I can't.

1122
01:23:27.877 --> 01:23:28.632
Come on.

1123
01:25:28.727 --> 01:25:29.710
Aah!

1124
01:25:31.682 --> 01:25:32.558
Aah!

1125
01:25:37.976 --> 01:25:38.623
Oh!

1126
01:27:34.989 --> 01:27:37.440
I don't want you. Just her.

1127
01:27:39.057 --> 01:27:39.837
You understand.

1128
01:27:40.554 --> 01:27:41.644
It's strictly business.

1129
01:27:43.432 --> 01:27:44.816
You should have taken the money.

1130
01:27:49.381 --> 01:27:50.444
You know what I like about you?

1131
01:27:51.952 --> 01:27:52.888
You're tall.

1132
01:27:53.180 --> 01:27:53.761
Oh!

1133
01:28:13.136 --> 01:28:13.635
Larner.

1134
01:28:13.827 --> 01:28:14.556
This is Caulfield.

1135
01:28:14.748 --> 01:28:15.823
Where have you been?

1136
01:28:16.015 --> 01:28:18.356
I don't have time to explain. Listen.

1137
01:28:18.547 --> 01:28:20.543
Our friend Dahlbeck works for Leo Watts.

1138
01:28:20.735 --> 01:28:22.424
We wound up on a train.

1139
01:28:22.654 --> 01:28:25.340
The train's stopped at a siding.
I'm calling you from a farmhouse.

1140
01:28:25.532 --> 01:28:27.224
I'm about 100 miles from Vancouver.

1141
01:28:27.605 --> 01:28:28.334
The woman is safe.

1142
01:28:28.526 --> 01:28:29.830
I've contacted the Canadian authorities.

1143
01:28:30.022 --> 01:28:31.404
They'll be here any minute.

1144
01:28:31.673 --> 01:28:32.402
Get in touch with them.

1145
01:28:32.632 --> 01:28:33.438
Meet us at the border.

1146
01:28:33.630 --> 01:28:35.656
I'm on my way.

1147
01:28:38.712 --> 01:28:41.932
And then the man told
Mr. Tarlow not to be afraid.

1148
01:28:42.933 --> 01:28:45.066
I remember he said.
"Michael. You're acting

1149
01:28:45.258 --> 01:28:46.740
as though you think I'll harm you."

1150
01:28:48.177 --> 01:28:50.693
And. uh. then he told Mr. Tarlow

1151
01:28:50.693 --> 01:28:52.661
That he was to go back to New York

1152
01:28:52.661 --> 01:28:56.126
And pay back all the money he owed.

1153
01:28:56.126 --> 01:28:58.485
Then he started to walk toward the door.

1154
01:28:58.485 --> 01:29:02.339
And he stopped and turned around
and said.

1155
01:29:02.339 --> 01:29:03.900
"Michael. I lied."

1156
01:29:03.900 --> 01:29:06.437
Then the other man that was with him

1157
01:29:06.437 --> 01:29:09.868
turned around and pulled out a gun...

1158
01:29:09.868 --> 01:29:12.795
and shot Mr. Tarlow.

1159
01:29:13.350 --> 01:29:15.382
Did Mr. Tarlow call anybody
in the room by name?

1160
01:29:15.382 --> 01:29:19.047
Yes. he called the man Leo.

1161
01:29:19.414 --> 01:29:21.260
And did you get a clear look at
the man named Leo?

1162
01:29:21.640 --> 01:29:22.153
Yes.

1163
01:29:22.830 --> 01:29:24.531
- Could you identify him?
- Yes.

1164
01:29:24.787 --> 01:29:26.859
- Is he in the courtroom at this time?
- Yes.

1165
01:29:26.951 --> 01:29:27.941
Could you point to him?

1166
01:29:28.663 --> 01:29:29.341
Yes.

1167
01:29:31.503 --> 01:29:32.788
It's that man sitting right there.

1168
01:29:39.485 --> 01:29:40.844
Let the record state that the witness

1169
01:29:41.481 --> 01:29:42.963
Has pointed to Mr. Leo Watts.

1170
01:29:44.321 --> 01:29:46.012
Thank you. Miss Hunnicut.
No further questions.

1171
01:29:47.305 --> 01:30:47.758
